author: Adam Savage’s Tested
description:
We test ane review Bambu Lab's newest 3D printer: the H2S single nozzle version of the H2D flagship. In many ways, this is the follow up to the X1C that we were expecting: a high-speed Core XY printer with a much larger build volume--even bigger than that of the dual nozzle H2D. What we didn't expect was the price!

Find the Bambu Lab H2S here: https://www.matterhackers.com/store/c/3d-printers/bambu-lab-3d-printers?aff=7553
Disclosure: This product was sent to us by the manufacturer for purposes of review and is not sponsored. 

Shot by Josh Self and edited by Norman Chan
Music by Jinglepunks

author: Adam Savage’s Tested
description:
At the National Park Service museum conservation lab post-graduate fellow Maeve O'Shea introduces Adam Savage to a deteriorated 1860s flag with a very colorful history. 

The flag featured is owned by the Gettysburg Foundation and comes from the Collection of the Civil War Museum of Philadelphia.

National Park Museum Conservation Lab: https://www.nps.gov/subjects/hfc/museum-conservation-services.htm
title: Why This U.S. Flag Only Flew for a Month
